 instance), but not everyone can get those.  A profile that maintained ~1200 ac (despite the massive hits for weight allowances) is what I'd be looking for.  Something where carrying an additional 20lbs of coins or loot would have no effect on you.<br><br>Please hold the "if you don't want to worry about weight, you picked the wrong class" comments.  I'm just wondering if this is currently feasible. <p><p align="center"><img border="0" src="http://www.nvo.com/kvroman/nss-folder/pictures/att00002.jpg"  width="213" height="182"></p><p align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77485">Bulfraug</a>, 52 Troll Warrior<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=54253">Carpenter</a>, 54 Gnomish Badass<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=54255">Yael</a>, 58 Iksar Monk</p></body></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usehnsuch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sehnsuch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/30/02 5:42:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11676.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ignoring the weight allowance for monks?</span><hr size=1> That idea would only work on items with HUGE AC. And that only happens in VT, etc. Therefore, there are two glaring, hilarious flaws.<br><br><br>1) If you're a VT monk, you're AC is so high you'd piss in your pants for a chance to switch out AC for HP. Mostly due to the fact that all VT monks have more AC than the cap, and thus, more than they want.<br><br>2) Ever seen a VT warrior? Obviously high AC warrior items would be an example of what you mean. Well, those warriors weight 1 to 2 pounds. Even if they do weigh more, it's less than the monk 24 pound limit. Strange, but all VT gear, even plat, weighs 0.<br><br>NOTE: I don't mean to talk about VT so much, just an easy phrase to say, and most VT capable guilds are the uberguilds of the server.<br><br>I guess you're idea does hold some merit, if you're talking about normal overlooked items. But I find it unlikely there would be enough AC to offset the AC loss. Also, it's hard to find out about heavy items that have been overlooked, as EQ has been out quite a long time, and played to death. Monks are popular of certain items they were never truly meant to use, such as Barbed Dragonscale Boots. <p><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=285468"> Roemy </a></br>50 Monk</br>Prexus</br>Got Rage?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugaintumijo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gain Tumijo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/30/02 8:42:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11676.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ignoring the weight allowance for monks?</span><hr size=1> From what I understand about weight, being over the weight allowance causes you to block and dodge less effectively. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=229669">Gain An'Sydnor</a><br>Human Warlord <br>Knights of Winters Past <BR>aka KoWPie ;)<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=268424 ">Gaine </a><br>48 Iksar Monkey</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usehnsuch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sehnsuch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/30/02 10:01:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11676.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ignoring the weight allowance for monks?</span><hr size=1> I don't believe it. It's been a consensus around here that's just speculation, and probably untrue. <p><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=285468"> Roemy </a></br>50 Monk</br>Prexus</br>Endless Faith</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufiramas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Firamas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 4:32:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11676.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ignoring the weight allowance for monks?</span><hr size=1> I took out a couple million copper from the bank to test it once.. I was *well* over the softcap even fully weighed down.  <br><br>I've also heard about weight affecting avoidance AC, but there's no hard evidence to support that yet.  If it's true it'd be a great reason not to exceed the cap.  If it's just speculation, then the cap means nothing for a lot of high end monks. <p>--------------------------------<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5254">Firamas Shadowstrike</a>  [<a href="http://www.enlighteneddark.org">Enlightened Dark</a>]<BR>Grandmasta Leezard<BR>Tarew Marr</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=11676.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.sh